Six Viet boatpeople stage breakout from HK camp . Six Vietnamese boatpeople staged a breakout from a Hong Kong detention camp on Friday , the British colony ' s government said . Four had been captured by police and two were still missing , a government information service officer told Reuters . Police were sweeping the hills around the Whitehead detention centre in Hong Kong ' s rural New Territories for the two escapees , the officer said . She said guards at the centre had quickly alerted police about the breakout . Last year , the Whitehead camp was the scene of a massive breakout and rioting . 
